  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Anemia continues to be a major public health problem in many regions of the world and it is
      still not clear which strategy is more effective in children population in terms of adherence
      and efficacy. The objective was to evaluate the efficacy and acceptance of several strategies
      that have been recently recommended to treat anemia on anemic children (6 to 43 mo):Iron
      supplement, iron+folic acid supplement, a multiple micronutrients supplement a micronutrient
      fortified complementary food in the form of porridge powder or zinc+iron+ascorbic acid
      fortified water.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
